What you need to know:

For  one who started playing the game barely three years ago with no golf kit of his own, the 29-year-old player who lost hearing at an early age following a fall from a tree has achieved many firstsHe became the first amateur golfer to qualify for 2021 Magical Kenya Open Championship, having won the 2020 Kenya Amateur Match Play Championship against able-bodied opponentsHe credits his steady rise to support from fellow golfers, particularly his Vet Lab club mate Kihara and Railway’s Njoroge